casebody.data:
NOAH W. EUBANKS v. NEWPORT SHIPS, CONTINENTAL CASUALTY COMPANY, and FLORIDA INDUSTRIAL COMMISSION. 22 So. (2nd) 155

January Term, 1945

May 4, 1945 Division B Atkinson & Atkinson, for appellant. Ausley, Collins & Truett, for appellees. PER CURIAM:

The judgment appealed from is affirmed on authority of Travelers Insurance Co., et al., v. Shepard, et al., decided February 20, 1945, (Fla.), 20 So. 2nd 903, and S. H. Kress & Co., et al., v. Burkes, 153 Fla. 868, 16 So. (2nd) 106.

It is so ordered.

CHAPMAN, C. J., BROWN, THOMAS and SEBRING, JJ., concur.
